        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 17 at 4:10PM CDT by NWS Amarillo TX</headline>
        <description>At 409 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 15
miles northwest of Lora, or 16 miles north of Miami, moving north at
10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Lora.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
